  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain in OpenJDK consists of multiple layers spanning Java and HotSpot C++ code.\n\n**Java Layer (Parent-First Delegation):**\n\n1. **ClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java): The foundational class that defines the delegation model. The protected loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) method (line 534) implements the parent-first delegation pattern: it first checks if the class is already loaded via findLoadedClass(), then delegates to the parent class loader if one exists, and finally calls findClass() to locate the class itself.\n\n2. **BuiltinClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java): The base class for the three built-in loaders, extending SecureClassLoader. The module-aware loadClassOrNull(String cn, boolean resolve) method (line 589) refines the delegation strategy: it first identifies if the class's package is part of a module (via findLoadedModule), delegates to the appropriate module loader if necessary, delegates to the parent loader, and finally searches the class path. The findClass(String cn) method (line 512) locates classes in modules or on the class path. The loadModule(ModuleReference mref) method (line 224) registers modules to the loader.\n\n3. **ClassLoaders.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java): Creates and maintains the three built-in loaders initialized in a static block (line 63). BootClassLoader (line 131) is the topmost loader with no parent, delegating to JLA.findBootstrapClassOrNull() for actual class loading. PlatformClassLoader (line 146) has BootClassLoader as parent and loads platform modules. AppClassLoader (line 161) has PlatformClassLoader as parent and loads application classes from the class path.\n\n**Native Layer (Caching and Resolution):**\n\n4. **classLoader.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp): The HotSpot C++ implementation providing native class loading support. It manages performance counters for class loading statistics and integrates with the native class loading mechanism for bootstrap classes.\n\n5. **systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.cpp): The cache layer that stores loaded classes. Each ClassLoaderData maintains a concurrent hash table (Dictionary) with a fixed number of buckets. The static resolve_or_fail(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader, bool throw_error) method (line 92) and resolve_or_null(Symbol* class_name, Handle class_loader) method (line 100) resolve classes and cache them in the dictionary. The SystemDictionary_lock is held for all additions into class loader dictionaries, and placeholders are temporarily placed during class loading to detect circular dependencies.\n\n**Delegation Chain Summary:**\n\nWhen a class is requested: loadClass() → parent.loadClass() (if parent exists) → findClass() → For BuiltinClassLoaders: check modules → check parent (with module awareness) → search class path → HotSpot SystemDictionary caches the result. This ensures the parent-first delegation model while supporting the Java module system."
}

